item.title: Ronnie Lane
item.description: Ronald Frederick Lane was an English musician, songwriter, and producer who is best known as the bass guitarist and founding member of two prominent English rock and roll bands: Small Faces (1965–69) and subsequently Faces (1969–73). With Small Faces he was nicknamed 'Plonk'. After their breakup and re-formation as Faces, he acquired the nickname 'Three-Piece'.
